self otherwise?=C2=A0

=C2=A0

For tonight=E2=80=99s issue,
Julie Davich spoke to the leadership at Gurr Johns about their plans for gr=
owth, now that the transatlantic appraisal and advisory firm has announced =
a new C.E.O. The news is on theme with everything we=E2=80=99ve been tellin=
g you about the strength and potential growth of the private market. Then, =
I=E2=80=99m going to look at two versions of a Lucas Cranach painting that =
are coming up in February=E2=80=99s New York Old Master auctions. I was tip=
ped
off to these doppelg=C3=A4ngers by a contemporary art advisor. (That=E2=80=
=99s a whole other thing: Lately, contemporary advisors and collectors have=
 been paying close attention to the old masters market.) Finally, I look at=
 a lawsuit filed last month on behalf of Peter Beard=E2=80=99s studio. It=
=E2=80=99s a case study in how the market regulates itself.

