line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">When I caught up with <strong>Charlie</strong>
<strong>Horne</strong>, president of the appraisal and advisory firm Gurr J=
ohns, he was on his way to the Heckerling Institute on Estate Planning in O=
rlando. Heckerling, as the gathering is known in the industry, is about as =
exciting as you=E2=80=99d imagine for a conference of estate lawyers and ba=
nkers=E2=80=94but the event does offer an essential glad-handing opportunit=
y for auction houses and appraisal firms. Charlie will no doubt be touting =
the news that <strong>Maarten</strong> <strong>ten</strong>
<strong>Holder</strong> is joining Gurr Johns as C.E.O. to oversee the firm=
=E2=80=99s growth strategy, first in the U.S. and then globally.=C2=A0=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Ten Holder spent nearly 25 years at Sotheby=E2=80=
=99s, shuttling back and forth in operational roles between Europe and New =
York before taking over the global luxury business and then the classic car=
 division after the acquisition of RM. Most recently, he was at Bonhams
for three years heading up its <em>very</em> British =E2=80=9CMotoring depa=
rtment.=E2=80=9D He arrived at Gurr Johns last week after a six-month garde=
ning leave.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p =
style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Gurr Johns=E2=80=99 core business for=
 the past 110 years has been appraisals=E2=80=94a somewhat limited service =
offering, given the time and expertise involved, as well as the general fru=
gality of clients. Indeed, most collectors view the process as a necessary =
evil to
placate their insurance companies and tax advisors, rather than as an inves=
tment of sorts. Gurr Johns also offers advisory services, which comprise on=
ly a small part of the business and are usually just an upsell on the appra=
isal relationships. Unsurprisingly, ten Holder is expected to operationaliz=
e and expand this channel.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The firm, as I discussed wi=
th ten Holder, is also looking to launch a brokerage
offering. Gurr Johns inaugurated its new Paris office this past fall with a=
 private selling exhibition of 20 cubist portraits=E2=80=94including a <str=
ong>Picasso</strong> paper collage that sold at Christie=E2=80=99s in 2014 =
for $4.3 million=E2=80=94and its London team has mounted shows of primary-m=
arket works for the past few years. That=E2=80=99s not a big deal for a fir=
m that appraised $15 billion in art last year and has a massive database to=
 match sellers with buyers. As Marion
<a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2Uktx=
clJLZ0dVWjFCUDloNWxNQVRIWmkxYkkzaz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3Mvd2h=
5LXRoZS1hcnQtbWFya2V0LWhhcy1lbnRlcmVkLWEtcHJpdmF0ZS1zYWxlcy1lcmEvP3V0bV9jYW=
1wYWlnbj1XYWxsK1Bvd2VyKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjE0JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1d=
G1fY29udGVudD1XYWxsK1Bvd2VyKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjE0JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAw=
MjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cdTA=
wMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0Mm=
